The input `triangle` is not null.
The input `triangle` is a valid triangle array.
The length of `triangle` is greater than or equal to 1.
The length of `triangle[0]` is equal to 1.
The length of `triangle[i]` is equal to `triangle[i-1] + 1` for all `i` from 1 to `triangle.length - 1`.
The values in `triangle` are within the range of -10^4 to 10^4.
